JOHANNESBURG The Constitutional Court has dismissed an appeal by the Department of Environmental Affairs to keep a moratorium on the domestic trade in rhino horn, according to court documents seen by Reuters on Wednesday.READ: Police probe Mahlobo rhino poaching allegationsPelham Jones, chairman of the Private Rhino Owners Association which was one of the respondents in the case, told Reuters this meant that the sale of rhino horns was legal in South Africa.A global ban in the horn trade, which is regulated by a UN convention, remains in place.Reuters